Rating: 0
First of all, this dish looked so pretty and was practically effortless to make. The only thing that takes time is allowing the orzo to cook, which takes less time than pasta. This dish is also very delicious and the final product/taste look deceptively labor intensive. Two things to note: definitely add much more orzo as there is a large amount of tomato and olive oil for the amount of orzo the recipe calls for and adding more extends the dish. Also, I used about a tablespoon of dried dill from a spice bottle rather than fresh dill. It still tasted great and 1 tablespoon was a great substitute if more orzo is added. The red of the tomatoes and green of the dill makes this a very festive dish for christmas, if good tomatoes could be procured.

