Okay, I sure didn't want this to taste like a lemon cake or any other pastry as someone scared me below. . . nonetheless, we thought this was refreshing, tasty and went very well with the oregano grilled shrimp - as these 2 recipes are mediterranean-like. Oh yea - I did change it up only because I didn't have enough dill or any feta. Used about TWO tsp of finely grated fluffy lemon zest; about 1/4 cup chopped dill; roasted the cherry tomatoes in olive oil, kosher salt and pepper first. Even used a bit of the roasted tomato juice from the pan and mixed it in. And since the oven was on from roasting the tomatoes, I toasted some pinenuts to roll in at the end. Was yummy even without the cheese.

